The boolean data type declares a variable with the value either true or false.

    Java Operator       Math Symbol         Name                        Example (radius = 5)    Result
    <                       <               Less then                   radius < 0              false
    <=                      <=              Less then or equal to       radius <= 0             false
    >                       >               Greater then                radius > 0              true
    >=                      >=              Greater then or equal to    radius >= 0             true
    ==                      =               Equal to                    radius == 0             false
    !=                                      Not equal to                radius != 0             true

EXAMPLE: AdditionQuiz.java